Education Minister Blade Nzimande, outlines the ramifications of matric results on the Post school Education and Training sector in South Africa. JOHANNESBURG - Education Minister Blade Nzimande, outlines the ramifications of matric results on the Post school Education and Training sector in South Africa. The availability and opportunities that higher learning institutions provide will also be discussed. On Tuesday, 17 January, Basic Education Minister Angie Motshekga, announced the 2019 public school matric pass rate. The class of 2019 achieved a 81,3 percent pass rate.  